{"articles_and_essays": null, "calendar_url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/?st=calendar", "cite_this": {"apa": "(1914, January 30)  <cite>The Ocala evening star</cite>. Retrieved from the Library of Congress, https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/1914-01-30/ed-1/.", "chicago": "<cite>The Ocala evening star</cite>. (Ocala, FL), Jan. 30 1914. https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/1914-01-30/ed-1/.", "mla": "<cite>The Ocala evening star</cite>. (Ocala, FL) 30 Jan. 1914, p. 5. Retrieved from the Library of Congress, www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/1914-01-30/ed-1/."}, "fulltext_service": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_beaty_ver01/data/sn84027621/00295865908/1914013001/0198.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "item": {"_version_": 1855499559388577792, "access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/1914-01-30/ed-1/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84027621/1914-01-30/ed-1/"], "batch": ["fu_beaty_ver01"], "call_number": ["Newspaper"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/florida/", "2/united states/florida/marion/", "3/united states/florida/marion/ocala/"], "contributor_names": ["University of Florida"], "contributors": [{"university of florida": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=contributor:university+of+florida&fo=json"}], "created_published": ["Ocala, Fla., January 30, 1914"], "date": "1914-01-30", "date_issued": "1914-01-30", "dates": [{"1914-01-30": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?dates=1914-01-30/1914-01-30&fo=json"}], "dates_of_publication": "1895-1943", "description": ["Ocala, Fla."], "digital_id": ["https://www.loc.gov/chroniclingamerica/lccn/sn84027621/issues", "http://ufdc.ufl.edu/UF00075908"], "digitized": true, "digitized_label": "Present", "display_offsite": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-01-27T16:57:47.864Z", "extract_urls": ["file:/service/ndnp//fu/batch_fu_beaty_ver01/data/sn84027621/00295865908/1914013001/1914013001_1.xml#ndnp/fu"], "format": [{"newspaper": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=original_format:newspaper&fo=json"}], "genre": ["Newspapers"], "group": ["ndnp/fu", "university-of-florida-awardee"], "hassegments": true, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/1914-01-30/ed-1/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_beaty_ver01:data:sn84027621:00295865908:1914013001:0194/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=285&w=209", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_beaty_ver01:data:sn84027621:00295865908:1914013001:0194/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=571&w=418", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_beaty_ver01:data:sn84027621:00295865908:1914013001:0194/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1143&w=837"], "index": 5, "item": {"batch": ["fu_beaty_ver01"], "call_number": ["Newspaper"], "contributor_names": ["University of Florida"], "created_published": ["Ocala, Fla., January 30, 1914"], "date": "1895", "date_issued": "1914-01-30", "dates": ["1914-01-30"], "digital_id": ["https://www.loc.gov/chroniclingamerica/lccn/sn84027621/issues", "http://ufdc.ufl.edu/UF00075908"], "digitized_label": "Present", "format": ["newspaper"], "genre": ["Newspapers"], "language": ["eng"], "library_of_congress_control_number": "sn84027621", "location": ["Ocala (Fla.)", "Marion County (Fla.)", "Florida--Marion County", "Florida--Ocala"], "medium": "8 pages", "newspaper_title": ["The Ocala evening star"], "notes": ["Daily (except Sunday)", "Began in 1895; ceased in 1943.", "Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection.", "Description based on: Vol. 1, no. 5 (June 24, 1895).", "Latest issue consulted: Vol. no. 46 (Aug. 28, 1943)."], "other_formats": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp//fu/batch_fu_beaty_ver01/data/sn84027621/00295865908/1914013001/1914013001_1.xml", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn84027621/marcxml"], "other_title": ["Evening star", "Star"], "place_of_publication": "Ocala, Fla.", "raw_lccn": "sn 84027621 ", "reel_numbers": ["00295865908"], "source_group": "ndnp/fu", "subjects": ["Ocala (Fla.)--Newspapers", "Marion County (Fla.)--Newspapers", "Florida--Marion County", "Florida--Ocala", "United States--Florida--Marion--Ocala"], "summary": ["In 1895, the Ocala (FL) Evening Star [LCCN: sn84027621] surfaced as a rival publication to the Ocala (FL) Banner [LCCN: sn88074815]. These two titles subsequently merged into one publication on September 1, 1943. The resulting Ocala (FL) Star-Banner [LCCN: sn78002071] has remained the daily newspaper in Marion County (FL) since that time. The Ocala Evening Star was also published from 1897 in a weekly edition, the Ocala (FL) Weekly Star [LCCN: sn84027622]. R.N. Dosh, editor of the Ocala Evening Star in the 1920s and 1930s, gave an address to the Ocala Rotary Club, recalling by-gone editors and rival publications, chiefest of whom was Col. Frank E. Harris of the Ocala Banner in the 1890s. He also remembered that the \"Star first saw the light of day in the press room of the Florida Baptist Witness ... the first editor was A.H. Harding ...\" The Florida Baptist Witness (Ocala, FL) LCCN sn95026767], which began publishing in 1884, was the weekly newspaper of the Florida Baptist Convention, an organ of the Southern Baptist Convention. A variant edition of the same title continues (ca. 2008) to publish. Ocala (FL) is the seat of Marion County (FL) government. The Freeze of 1894 dramatically changed the Ocala into which the Ocala Evening Star was born. The Freeze devastated the citrus industry in Marion County. Between 1895 and 1943, other forms of agriculture took the place of citrus while tourism in the area grew. The Silver Springs theme park, known for its crystal clear waters, would do its part like no other attraction in pre-World War II Marion County. The County remained primarily agricultural until after the war, when its character would again change dramatically.--E. Kesse, University of Florida Digital Library Center."], "title": "The Ocala evening star (Ocala, Fla.), January 30, 1914"}, "language": ["english"], "languages": [{"english": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=language:english&fo=json"}], "library_of_congress_control_number": "sn84027621", "location": ["ocala", "marion", "marion county", "florida", "united states"], "location_city": ["ocala"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["marion"], "location_state": ["florida"], "locations": [{"florida": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:florida&fo=json"}, {"marion": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:marion&fo=json"}, {"marion county": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:marion+county&fo=json"}, {"ocala": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:ocala&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:united+states&fo=json"}], "locations_city": [{"ocala": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location_city:ocala&fo=json"}], "locations_country": [{"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location_country:united+states&fo=json"}], "locations_county": [{"marion": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location_county:marion&fo=json"}], "locations_state": [{"florida": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location_state:florida&fo=json"}], "medium": "8 pages", "method": "mets_filesec", "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg"], "newspaper_title": ["The Ocala evening star"], "notes": ["Daily (except Sunday)", "Began in 1895; ceased in 1943.", "Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection.", "Description based on: Vol. 1, no. 5 (June 24, 1895).", "Latest issue consulted: Vol. no. 46 (Aug. 28, 1943)."], "number": ["1", "sn84027621", "00295865908"], "number_edition": ["1"], "number_lccn": ["sn84027621"], "number_reel": ["00295865908"], "numeric_shelf_id": 191401301, "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_formats": [{"label": "MODSXML Record", "link": "//tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp//fu/batch_fu_beaty_ver01/data/sn84027621/00295865908/1914013001/1914013001_1.xml"}, {"label": "MARCXML Record", "link": "//lccn.loc.gov/sn84027621/marcxml"}], "other_title": ["Evening star", "Star"], "partof": [{"count": 8030, "title": "the ocala evening star (ocala, fla.) 1895-1943", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=partof:the+ocala+evening+star+%28ocala,+fla.%29+1895-1943&fo=json"}, {"count": 3203926, "title": "chronicling america", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/chronicling-america/?fo=json"}, {"count": 3225157, "title": "serial and government publications division", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=partof:serial+and+government+publications+division&fo=json"}], "partof_collection": ["chronicling america"], "partof_division": ["serial and government publications division"], "partof_title": ["the ocala evening star (ocala, fla.) 1895-1943"], "place_of_publication": "Ocala, Fla.", "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "raw_lccn": "sn 84027621 ", "reel_numbers": ["00295865908"], "resources": [{"files": 8, "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_beaty_ver01:data:sn84027621:00295865908:1914013001:0194/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84027621/1914-01-30/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "rights": ["<p>The Library of Congress believes that the newspapers in Chronicling America are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.45633, "shard": "04", "shelf_id": "sn84027621, 1914-01-30, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/fu", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["ocala", "marion", "marion county (fla.)", "marion county", "newspapers", "florida", "ocala (fla.)", "united states"], "subject_headings": ["Ocala (Fla.)--Newspapers", "Marion County (Fla.)--Newspapers", "Florida--Marion County", "Florida--Ocala", "United States--Florida--Marion--Ocala"], "subjects": [{"florida": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:florida&fo=json"}, {"marion": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:marion&fo=json"}, {"marion county": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:marion+county&fo=json"}, {"marion county (fla.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:marion+county+%28fla.%29&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"ocala": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:ocala&fo=json"}, {"ocala (fla.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:ocala+%28fla.%29&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "summary": ["In 1895, the Ocala (FL) Evening Star [LCCN: sn84027621] surfaced as a rival publication to the Ocala (FL) Banner [LCCN: sn88074815]. These two titles subsequently merged into one publication on September 1, 1943. The resulting Ocala (FL) Star-Banner [LCCN: sn78002071] has remained the daily newspaper in Marion County (FL) since that time. The Ocala Evening Star was also published from 1897 in a weekly edition, the Ocala (FL) Weekly Star [LCCN: sn84027622]. R.N. Dosh, editor of the Ocala Evening Star in the 1920s and 1930s, gave an address to the Ocala Rotary Club, recalling by-gone editors and rival publications, chiefest of whom was Col. Frank E. Harris of the Ocala Banner in the 1890s. He also remembered that the \"Star first saw the light of day in the press room of the Florida Baptist Witness ... the first editor was A.H. Harding ...\" The Florida Baptist Witness (Ocala, FL) LCCN sn95026767], which began publishing in 1884, was the weekly newspaper of the Florida Baptist Convention, an organ of the Southern Baptist Convention. A variant edition of the same title continues (ca. 2008) to publish. Ocala (FL) is the seat of Marion County (FL) government. The Freeze of 1894 dramatically changed the Ocala into which the Ocala Evening Star was born. The Freeze devastated the citrus industry in Marion County. Between 1895 and 1943, other forms of agriculture took the place of citrus while tourism in the area grew. The Silver Springs theme park, known for its crystal clear waters, would do its part like no other attraction in pre-World War II Marion County. The County remained primarily agricultural until after the war, when its character would again change dramatically.--E. Kesse, University of Florida Digital Library Center."], "timestamp": "2026-01-27T19:31:13.218Z", "title": "The Ocala evening star (Ocala, Fla.), January 30, 1914", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/1914-01-30/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn84027621", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/138bf5d8-269e-5a47-85dc-87d3adcd04a2"], "batch": ["fu_anderson_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1895", "description": ["In 1895, the Ocala (FL) Evening Star [LCCN: sn84027621] surfaced as a rival publication to the Ocala (FL) Banner [LCCN: sn88074815]. These two titles subsequently merged into one publication on September 1, 1943. The resulting Ocala (FL) Star-Banner [LCCN: sn78002071] has remained the daily newspaper in Marion County (FL) since that time. The Ocala Evening Star was also published from 1897 in a weekly edition, the Ocala (FL) Weekly Star [LCCN: sn84027622]. R.N. Dosh, editor of the Ocala Evening Star in the 1920s and 1930s, gave an address to the Ocala Rotary Club, recalling by-gone editors and rival publications, chiefest of whom was Col. Frank E. Harris of the Ocala Banner in the 1890s. He also remembered that the \"Star first saw the light of day in the press room of the Florida Baptist Witness ... the first editor was A.H. Harding ...\" The Florida Baptist Witness (Ocala, FL) LCCN sn95026767], which began publishing in 1884, was the weekly newspaper of the Florida Baptist Convention, an organ of the Southern Baptist Convention. A variant edition of the same title continues (ca. 2008) to publish. Ocala (FL) is the seat of Marion County (FL) government. The Freeze of 1894 dramatically changed the Ocala into which the Ocala Evening Star was born. The Freeze devastated the citrus industry in Marion County. Between 1895 and 1943, other forms of agriculture took the place of citrus while tourism in the area grew. The Silver Springs theme park, known for its crystal clear waters, would do its part like no other attraction in pre-World War II Marion County. The County remained primarily agricultural until after the war, when its character would again change dramatically.--E. Kesse, University of Florida Digital Library Center."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:17.113Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-15", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-15"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [29.189311, -82.137789], "location": ["ocala", "marion", "marion county", "florida", "united states"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-82.137789, 29.189311], "number": ["1", "new york hist soc, newsp proj", "online resource", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/1895-06-24/ed-1/", "2025-11-07t12:44:30.100000", "sn84027621", "sn84027622", "11319113", "2025-05-23t21:30:26", "8032", "1943-8869", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/1922-12-30/ed-1/", "original"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Evening star", "Star"], "partof": ["catalog", "the ocala evening star (ocala, fla.) 1895-1943", "chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 78.05022, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["ocala", "marion", "marion county (fla.)", "marion county", "newspapers", "florida", "ocala (fla.)", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-07-22T07:38:06.169Z", "title": "The Ocala evening star", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84027621/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88074815/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn88074815", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/d3469f3a-2112-5e5e-9382-8935a851c245"], "batch": ["fu_edugator_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1883", "description": ["The East Florida Banner [LCCN: sn84022783] first started publishing weekly in Marion County, Florida in 1866. The Florida Newspaper Chronology, promulgated by David Shedden at the Poynter Institute for Media Studies in St. Petersburg, FL, lists a variant for the initial appearance of the newspaper, the East Marion Banner [LCCN: not known to exist]. The East Florida Banner described itself as \"Democratic\" and as the \"Official Organ of the 5th Judicial Circuit\"-. It is the direct forerunner of today's Star-Banner [LCCN: sn95005532]. The East Florida Banner was sold to George W. Wilson in 1881, and renamed The Florida Banner-Lacon [LCCN: sn95047283], having merged with the Florida Lacon [LCCN: not known to exist]. In 1883, the name was changed to the Ocala (FL) Banner [LCCN: sn88074815]. In 1890, it became a daily newspaper. In 1895, the Ocala (FL) Evening Star [LCCN: sn84027621] surfaced as a rival publication to the Ocala Banner. They subsequently joined merged into one publication on September 1, 1943. The resulting Ocala (FL) Star-Banner [LCCN: sn78002071] has remained the daily newspaper in Marion County (FL) since that time. The Ocala Banner bore the alternate titles the Banner, the Daily Banner, and the Ocala Daily Banner. A daily edition, published between 1908 and 1920, is thought to have existed, but its title is unknown. Another daily edition, the Ocala Morning Banner was published between 1930 and 1943. R.N. Dosh, editor of the Ocala Evening Star in the 1920s and 1930s, gave an address to the Ocala Rotary Club, recalling by-gone editors and rival publications, chiefest of whom was Col. Frank E. Harris of the Ocala Banner in the 1890s. Frank E. Harris was sent to Florida to fight in the Seminole Wars. He later fought in the Civil War on the side of the Confederacy in the First Florida Infantry Regiment. Other editors included T.W. Harris and C.L. Bittinger. T.W. Harris also published the daily, except Mondays, Daily Item (Ocala, FL) [LCCN sn95026901], from 1885 through 1886 and the weekly Rural Free Press (Ocala, FL) [LCCN sn95072056] from 1886 through at least 1888. Before moving to Florida, C.L. Bittinger had served as a commander in the Grand Army of the Republic during the Civil War. His only known newspaper work was with the Ocala Banner. Ocala (FL) is the seat of Marion County (FL) government. The Freeze of 1894 dramatically changed Ocala, devastating the citrus industry in Marion County. Between 1883 and 1943, other forms of agriculture took the place of citrus while tourism in the area grew. The Silver Springs theme park, known for its crystal clear waters, would do its part like no other attraction in pre-World War II Marion County. The County remained primarily agricultural until after the war, when its character would again change dramatically. The Ocala Banner covered agriculture, tourism and civic issues. --E. Kesse, University of Florida Digital Library Center."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:17.596Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-10", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-10"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88074815/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [29.189311, -82.137789], "location": ["ocala", "marion", "marion county", "florida", "united states"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-82.137789, 29.189311], "number": ["1", "1074", "online resource", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2025-11-07t15:16:28.400000", "18660476", "sn95047284", "1943-8877", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88074815/1891-03-13/ed-1/", "2025-05-23t21:30:26", "microfilm service copy", "univ of virginia", "original", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88074815/1922-12-29/ed-1/", "center for res libr, newsp proj", "sn88074815", "sn95047283"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Ocala daily banner", "Daily banner", "Banner"], "partof": ["catalog", "chronicling america", "the ocala banner (ocala, marion county, fla.) 1883-194?", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "sc